ok sorry for the previous comment, i was very rude. i found a way to split them to single tracks just follow this tutorial: http://www.simplehelp.net/2009/03/02/how-to-split-a-single-flac-file-into-multiple-tracks/

I also found out that flac is best high quality you can get in audio files, flac means Free Lossless Audio Codec, it maintains the same quality as it is in the original cd, only the file is much much more bigger, but what the hell??! i take it back, this is the best carpenters torrent in the internet. long live the music.
